# Spec Pack conversation routing rules (mandatory)

As long as **even 1%** of the conversation may involve the AI SDLC/Spec Pack of this repository (e.g. mention`Spec Pack`、`.aisdlc/specs/`、`raw/solution/prd/prototype/demo`、`design/*`、`implementation/plan.md`、`spec-init/spec-context`etc.), must first be`skills/using-aisdlc/SKILL.md`As the **only router (Router)**, it determines the worker skill and product placement path to be used in the next step.

## Hard access control (cannot be skipped)

- **Context first, then read and write**: Any attempt to read or write the following path (or its sub-path) must be executed first`spec-context`and echoed in the conversation`FEATURE_DIR=...`; If it fails, it must stop and can only output "blocking reason + required input/next step".
  -`{FEATURE_DIR}/requirements/*`
  - `{FEATURE_DIR}/design/*`
  - `{FEATURE_DIR}/implementation/*`
  - `{REPO_ROOT}/demo/prototypes/{CURRENT_BRANCH}/*`- **No Guessing**: Do not "guess" based on the user's verbal path/branch name/screenshot`FEATURE_DIR`Or write files directly in the directory structure.
- **One stage at a time**: It is forbidden to mix PRD+prototype+Demo or plan+implementation together at one time; the router must be placed in stages and reflowed in a closed loop.

## Command and submission convention (default for this warehouse)

- **PowerShell**: Use multiple commands on the same line`;`, do not use`&&`.
- **Commit message**: If you need to generate git commit message, you must use Chinese.